name: Microservices_Project
description: This repository contains a microservices-based e-commerce system built with Spring Boot, Spring Security, and JWT authentication. The project is designed to demonstrate a typical microservices architecture, where each service is independent, has its own database, and communicates securely via JWT tokens.

name: talent-acquisition-microservices
description: The Career Portal Macroproject is a distributed system comprising multiple microservices for managing career-related operations. Built with Spring Boot, Axon Framework, and Eureka, it uses CQRS, Event Sourcing, and service discovery to deliver a scalable, event-driven architecture.

name: AngularMicroFrontendsAndMicroServices
description: 3 Microservices with a unified frontend of 3 Microfrontends based on Self Containted Systems architecture using a Postgresql Db each. The Microservices are build with Typescript/NestJs, Kotlin/SpringBoot, Java/SpringBoot and Angular frontends. They are communicating with Mqtt messaging.

name: Distributed-Blogging-Application-Test
description: A distributed system built with microservices to manage API routing, authentication, blogging, notifications, and user data. The system is containerized using Docker, orchestrated by Kubernetes, and connected through RabbitMQ for real-time inter-service communication.

name: profile-hub
description: Profile-Hub is a microservices-based user management system designed to handle user authentication, profile management, and activity logging. Built using Spring Boot and Spring Cloud, it offers a scalable and maintainable solution for managing user data and interactions.

name: EA-catalogservice
description: This project is a microservice API developed using .NET Core as part of the EA eCommerce system. It is responsible for managing the product catalog of the application. The service utilizes MongoDB for data storage, Redis for distributed caching, and pagination for efficient data retrieval.
